Authentication vs Authorization

| Aspect           | Authentication                                                                  | Authorization                                                                                                     |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------  | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Definition       | Verifies the identity of a user using credentials (e.g., username, password)    | Determines what actions or resources an authenticated user is allowed to access.                                  |
| Purpose          | Confirms "who the user is".                                                     | Determines "what the user is allowed to do".                                                                      |
| Process          | Identity verification.                                                          | Permission verification.                                                                                          |
| When It Happens  | First, before authorization.                                                    | After successful authentication.                                                                                  |
| Methods          | Username & Password, OTP, JWT, OAuth, Sessions, Biometrics.                     | Roles (ADMIN, USER), Permissions, Access Control Lists (ACL), Policies.                                           |
| Example          | Logging in using a username and password.                                       | Checking whether a user can access the Admin Dashboard or delete a record.                                        |
| Key Question     | "Who are you?"                                                                  | "What are you allowed to do?"                                                                                     |
| Result           | User identity is verified.                                                      | Access is granted or denied based on permissions.                                                                 |
| HTTP Status Code | 401 Unauthorized – Authentication failed due to missing or invalid credentials. | 403 Forbidden – Authentication succeeded, but the user does not have permission to access the requested resource. |

